Gemma 4 does audio. I ran both variants, E2B (2B) and E4B (4B), against all eight Open ASR Leaderboard short-form datasets. Performance is **decent on clean speech** and **unreliable on harder inputs**, so it's useful as a general-purpose capability and for understanding. **Don't swap it in for a dedicated ASR model.**

<div class="not-prose my-10 grid grid-cols-2 gap-5 sm:grid-cols-4">
